# Terraform Conventions

## File organization
- `main.tf` — provider, backend config
- `variables.tf` — all input variables
- `outputs.tf` — all outputs
- `vpc.tf`, `ecr.tf`, `ec2.tf`, `s3.tf`, `lambda.tf`, `dns.tf` — resource-specific files
- `github_oidc.tf` — CI/CD OIDC config
- `environments/*.tfvars` — environment-specific overrides
- `.build/` — generated artifacts (Lambda zip, layer zip) — gitignored

## Workflow
1. `terraform plan -var-file=environments/dev.tfvars -out=tfplan`
2. Review the plan output
3. `terraform apply tfplan`
4. Never `terraform apply` without a saved plan
5. Never edit state manually (`terraform state` commands only as last resort)

## Naming
- Resources: `${var.project}-{purpose}` (e.g., `danger-finger-ec2-role`)
- Use `name_prefix` for security groups to avoid naming conflicts

## Tags
All resources get default tags from the provider block:
- `Project = "danger-finger"`
- `Environment = var.environment`
- `ManagedBy = "terraform"`

## State
- Backend: S3 bucket `danger-finger-tfstate` with DynamoDB lock table `danger-finger-tflock`
- State is encrypted at rest
- Lock prevents concurrent modifications

## Conditional resources
- DNS/TLS: only when `domain_name` is set
- HTTPS/ACM: only when `enable_https = true`
- GitHub OIDC: only when `github_repo` is set
